item.title: Rate My Art
item.dc:creator: @davidi2 Davidi2
item.description:
@davidi2 wrote:

[quote=“Cole1497, post:19, topic:410005”][quote author=Davidi2 link=topic=511275.msg3712590#msg3712590 date=1313441151]
personally
[/quote]
Rules aren’t directed towards your opinions and feelings.[/quote]Ah. I’d agree but MITB has made it clear the type of people he wants here, even if they don’t break ‘the rules’ he’ll ban them because he dislikes those types of people. And just to be clear, in no way am I trying to say that this is me enforcing ‘rules’, because I think it’s pretty obvious none of the rules relate to this. This is just part of keeping the community clean.

[quote=“Slave Scyth, post:20, topic:410005”][quote author=Cole1497 link=topic=511275.msg3712928#msg3712928 date=1313453520]

personally

Rules aren’t directed towards your opinions and feelings.
[/quote]This, and some more of this.

Beyond that, rules are defensive; not offensive. You can’t just punish someone for something you think they MIGHT do. Muting him is completely uncalled for. You don’t throw someone in jail for owning a gun – you put them in jail when they shoot someone. Likewise, you don’t punish someone for OWNING a computer for hacking. Has he hacked anything that affects anything related to this site to your knowledge?[/quote]Actually, you can throw someone in jail for owning a gun if they aren’t supposed to. You can throw someone in jail for taking things that don’t belong to them. But have you ever heard of immigration laws? Most places have standards you must pass in order to become a citizen of their ‘community’, and if you don’t pass them, they can and will throw you out.

But I think I can say it’s defensive (even though it doesn’t need to be), he’s threatened me MULTIPLE times that’s he’s going to hack me, that he has the means to steal the database from this site, and more. And this was before I even muted him!

I’ll also mention that a member named ‘xx matty xx’ was banned just a few days ago for saying he could hack into the server (just like Javafire said he could!), I was being nice to not just perm ban him again.

To be honest I don’t even know why I muted instead of banned, the more I talk about it and talk to staff members the more it seems it should just be a perm.
